      "value": "<p><b>Source</b> <em>Melee Tactics Toolbox pg. 19</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><b>Cost</b> 10 gp <b>Weight</b> 4 lbs.</p><p><b>Damage</b> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <b>Critical</b> x3; <b>Range</b> -; <b>Type</b> P; <b>Special</b> grapple</p><p><b>Category</b> Two-Handed; <b>Proficiency</b> Simple</p><p><b>Weapon Groups</b> Axes</p><h3>Description</h3><p>This weapon acts as a kumade, but the handle consists of bamboo sections held together by a taut rope running through the center. Releasing the rope is a standard action that provokes attacks of opportunity and causes the weapon to collapse into a bundle that fits into a backpack. Reassembling the collapsible kumade requires a full-round action that provokes attacks of opportunity.</p>"
